  "texts": [
    "The study demonstrated the ability of the PSEVs to recover deleted disease-disease, disease-gene, compoundcompound, and compound-gene edges as well as infer new relationships between side effects and anatomy nodes.",
    "SPOKE now connects information from 41 biomedical databases and contains more than 21 node types and 55 edge types (83).",
    "In an updated version of SPOKE, with 400 K knowledge nodes and 7,535 SEPs, SPOKE was again embedded into EHRs using the same modified version of the PageRank algorithm to uncover the hidden patterns of information existing between the concepts in the patient records and the knowledge nodes (85).",
    "The PSEVs improved prediction of multiple sclerosis (MS) for 5,752 patients 3 years before diagnosis (AUC = 0.83 vs. AUC = 0.60 using only EHRs) and provided insight into the biological drivers of MS.",
    "The same SPOKE KG was used for the early detection of Parkinson's disease (86) with AUC accuracies of 0.77, 0.74, and 0.72 for 1, 3, and 5 years before diagnosis, respectively, and accuracies of 0.74, 0.70, and 0.66 in a validation cohort."
  ],
